HEADWORD: Allantoin
<hw>Al*lan"to*in</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A crystalline, transparent, colorless substance found in the
allantoic liquid of the fetal calf; -- formerly called <xex>allantoic
acid</xex> and <xex>amniotic acid</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

